## Comparison with Creative Commons

Software Commons is a bit like [Creative Commons][9] for software. Creative
Commons is explicitly [_not_ for software][10], but encompasses a range of
sharing practices for creative works. The Creative Commons motto is,
&ldquo;[Some rights reserved][11],&rdquo; and it includes licenses that
[restrict commercial use][12], and licenses that [restrict modification][13].
Software Commons encompasses a similar breadth of sharing practices for
software.

<img src="./img/cc.webp">

Unlike Software Commons, Creative Commons is an educational non-profit whose
main work is to publish licenses. Software Commons is [a multi-stakeholder
cooperative][1] that addresses [licensing][5] while also operating a [Fair
Share][6].

